37#define IRS_DNSCONF_MAGIC ISC_MAGIC('D', 'c', 'f', 'g')
38#define IRS_DNSCONF_VALID(c) ISC_MAGIC_VALID(c, IRS_DNSCONF_MAGIC)
39
40/*!
41 * configuration data structure
42 */
43
44struct irs_dnsconf {
45 unsigned int magic;
46 isc_mem_t *mctx;
47 irs_dnsconf_dnskeylist_t trusted_keylist;
48};
49
50static isc_result_t
51configure_dnsseckeys(irs_dnsconf_t *conf, cfg_obj_t *cfgobj,
52 dns_rdataclass_t rdclass)
53{
54 isc_mem_t *mctx = conf->mctx;
55 const cfg_obj_t *keys = NULL;
56 const cfg_obj_t *key, *keylist;
57 dns_fixedname_t fkeyname;
58 dns_name_t *keyname_base, *keyname;
59 const cfg_listelt_t *element, *element2;
60 isc_result_t result;
61 uint32_t flags, proto, alg;
62 const char *keystr, *keynamestr;
63 unsigned char keydata[4096];
64 isc_buffer_t keydatabuf_base, *keydatabuf;
65 dns_rdata_dnskey_t keystruct;
66 unsigned char rrdata[4096];
67 isc_buffer_t rrdatabuf;
68 isc_region_t r;
69 isc_buffer_t namebuf;
70 irs_dnsconf_dnskey_t *keyent;
71
72 cfg_map_get(cfgobj, "trusted-keys", &keys);
73 if (keys == NULL)
74 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
75
76 for (element = cfg_list_first(keys);
77 element != NULL;
78 element = cfg_list_next(element)) {
79 keylist = cfg_listelt_value(element);
80 for (element2 = cfg_list_first(keylist);
81 element2 != NULL;
82 element2 = cfg_list_next(element2))
83 {
84 keydatabuf = NULL;
85 keyname = NULL;
86
87 key = cfg_listelt_value(element2);
88
89 flags = cfg_obj_asuint32(cfg_tuple_get(key, "flags"));
90 proto = cfg_obj_asuint32(cfg_tuple_get(key,
91 "protocol"));
92 alg = cfg_obj_asuint32(cfg_tuple_get(key,
93 "algorithm"));
94 keynamestr = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(key,
95 "name"));
96
97 keystruct.common.rdclass = rdclass;
98 keystruct.common.rdtype = dns_rdatatype_dnskey;
99 keystruct.mctx = NULL;
100 ISC_LINK_INIT(&keystruct.common, link);
101
102 if (flags > 0xffff)
103 return (ISC_R_RANGE);
104 if (proto > 0xff)
105 return (ISC_R_RANGE);
106 if (alg > 0xff)
107 return (ISC_R_RANGE);
108 keystruct.flags = (uint16_t)flags;
109 keystruct.protocol = (uint8_t)proto;
110 keystruct.algorithm = (uint8_t)alg;
111
112 isc_buffer_init(&keydatabuf_base, keydata,
113 sizeof(keydata));
114 isc_buffer_init(&rrdatabuf, rrdata, sizeof(rrdata));
115
116 /* Configure key value */
117 keystr = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(key, "key"));
118 result = isc_base64_decodestring(keystr,
119 &keydatabuf_base);
120 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
121 return (result);
122 isc_buffer_usedregion(&keydatabuf_base, &r);
123 keystruct.datalen = r.length;
124 keystruct.data = r.base;
125
126 result = dns_rdata_fromstruct(NULL,
127 keystruct.common.rdclass,
128 keystruct.common.rdtype,
129 &keystruct, &rrdatabuf);
130 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
131 return (result);
132 isc_buffer_usedregion(&rrdatabuf, &r);
133 result = isc_buffer_allocate(mctx, &keydatabuf,
134 r.length);
135 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
136 return (result);
137 result = isc_buffer_copyregion(keydatabuf, &r);
138 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
139 goto cleanup;
140
141 /* Configure key name */
142 keyname_base = dns_fixedname_initname(&fkeyname);
143 isc_buffer_constinit(&namebuf, keynamestr,
144 strlen(keynamestr));
145 isc_buffer_add(&namebuf, strlen(keynamestr));
146 result = dns_name_fromtext(keyname_base, &namebuf,
147 dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
148 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
149 return (result);
150 keyname = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*keyname));
151 if (keyname == NULL) {
152 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
153 goto cleanup;
154 }
155 dns_name_init(keyname, NULL);
156 result = dns_name_dup(keyname_base, mctx, keyname);
157 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
158 goto cleanup;
159
160 /* Add the key data to the list */
161 keyent = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*keyent));
162 if (keyent == NULL) {
163 dns_name_free(keyname, mctx);
164 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
165 goto cleanup;
166 }
167 keyent->keyname = keyname;
168 keyent->keydatabuf = keydatabuf;
169
170 ISC_LIST_APPEND(conf->trusted_keylist, keyent, link);
171 }
172 }
173
174 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
175
176 cleanup:
177 if (keydatabuf != NULL)
178 isc_buffer_free(&keydatabuf);
179 if (keyname != NULL)
180 isc_mem_put(mctx, keyname, sizeof(*keyname));
181
182 return (result);
183}
184
185isc_result_t
186irs_dnsconf_load(isc_mem_t *mctx, const char *filename, irs_dnsconf_t **confp)
187{
188 irs_dnsconf_t *conf;
189 cfg_parser_t *parser = NULL;
190 cfg_obj_t *cfgobj = NULL;
191 isc_result_t result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
192
193 REQUIRE(confp != NULL && *confp == NULL);
194
195 conf = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*conf));
196 if (conf == NULL)
197 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
198
199 conf->mctx = mctx;
200 ISC_LIST_INIT(conf->trusted_keylist);
201
202 /*
203 * If the specified file does not exist, we'll simply with an empty
204 * configuration.
205 */
206 if (!isc_file_exists(filename))
207 goto cleanup;
208
209 result = cfg_parser_create(mctx, NULL, &parser);
210 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
211 goto cleanup;
212
213 result = cfg_parse_file(parser, filename, &cfg_type_dnsconf,
214 &cfgobj);
215 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
216 goto cleanup;
217
218 result = configure_dnsseckeys(conf, cfgobj, dns_rdataclass_in);
219
220 cleanup:
221 if (parser != NULL) {
222 if (cfgobj != NULL)
223 cfg_obj_destroy(parser, &cfgobj);
224 cfg_parser_destroy(&parser);
225 }
226
227 conf->magic = IRS_DNSCONF_MAGIC;
228
229 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
230 *confp = conf;
231 else
232 irs_dnsconf_destroy(&conf);
233
234 return (result);
235}
236
237void
238irs_dnsconf_destroy(irs_dnsconf_t **confp) {
239 irs_dnsconf_t *conf;
240 irs_dnsconf_dnskey_t *keyent;
241
242 REQUIRE(confp != NULL);
243 conf = *confp;
244 REQUIRE(IRS_DNSCONF_VALID(conf));
245
246 while ((keyent = ISC_LIST_HEAD(conf->trusted_keylist)) != NULL) {
247 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(conf->trusted_keylist, keyent, link);
248
249 isc_buffer_free(&keyent->keydatabuf);
250 dns_name_free(keyent->keyname, conf->mctx);
251 isc_mem_put(conf->mctx, keyent->keyname, sizeof(dns_name_t));
252 isc_mem_put(conf->mctx, keyent, sizeof(*keyent));
253 }
254
255 isc_mem_put(conf->mctx, conf, sizeof(*conf));
256
257 *confp = NULL;
258}
259
260irs_dnsconf_dnskeylist_t *
261irs_dnsconf_gettrustedkeys(irs_dnsconf_t *conf) {
262 REQUIRE(IRS_DNSCONF_VALID(conf));
263
264 return (&conf->trusted_keylist);
265}
